Class Paper

  • java.lang.Object
    • Paper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Paper>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Article, ConferencePaper

    public class Paper
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Paper>
    Project #2 CS 2334, Section 011 9/19/2013

    This class represents a paper. It has fields that represent its authors, title, the title of its serial publication, page numbers, date pubished, and a didgital identifier.

    Version:
    1.0

      • Paper

        public Paper(java.lang.String[] authors,
     java.lang.String title,
     java.lang.String serialTitle,
     int[] pageNumbers,
     java.lang.String date,
     java.lang.String digitalIdentifier)
        This constructor initializes all of the variables specific to a paper.
        Parameters:
        authors - an array of the author's names for this paper. The first author should be the primary one.
        title - the title of this paper.
        serialTitle - the title of the serial publishing this paper.
        pageNumbers - an array representing the first and last page numbers in the serial where this paper is found.
        date - the date this paper was published.
        digitalIdentifier - a digital identifier for the paper such as a URL.
        Conditions:
        POST - all instance variables are initialized.
